The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Basix deal
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Basix deal
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, Nov. 18: Hyderabad-based microfinance firm Basix has secured an income of 2.5 million euros (approximately Rs 16 crore) for its 1,500 clients through a carbon credit deal.         
	CTRAN, a Basix group firm, helped 1,500 households across Maharashtra, Gujarat and Karnataka, who had migrated from traditional water heaters to solar ones, to get a carbon emission reduction certificate through registration with the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change.         
	Germanys RWE Power Aktiengesellschaft has bought the carbon credits for 2.5 million euros.                                                                                                                                                                       
